  <exercise workspace="10%">
    <statement>
      <p>In base 6, a particular number can be made with 10 large cubes, 9 flats, 7 longs, and 5 small cubes.  What is this number in base 6? (Hint: the answer is NOT <m>10975_6 </m>. Try to solve this without converting to base 10)?</p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>

  <exercise workspace="10%">
    <statement>
      <p>My last digit is a 0 when I am represented in base-5 and a 1 when represented in base-2.  What is my last digit when represented base-10? Explain.</p>
